Founder and General Overseer, The Restoration Life Assembly International, Rev Dr Udochi Majesty Odikanwa, has called on Nigerians to embrace God and social hygiene as a way out of the current COVD-19 pandemic. Speaking after completing his second doctorate degree programme at the University of Abuja, Odikanwa, also urged Nigerians to increase their level of service to Christ and humanity, and to be disciplined, because the pandemic has shown that God is the super power. The cleric, who noted that the pandemic has brought lots of untold social and economic hardship to Nigeria and Nigerians, maintained that it is only divine intervention that would see the country through in this period, adding that even powerful nations of the world that possessed what it takes to curtail the virus could not succeed. He noted that Nigeria is deficient in internal sustainable development, tactical strategies of savings, family communism and artificial intelligence, adding however that credence must also be given to the frontline health workers, the Presidential Task Force (PTF) and other groups for their tenacity during the lockdown. Our reporter gathered that Rev Dr Udochi Majesty Odikanwa, a co-chairman of African Psychological Network and member of Nigerian Council of Educational Psychologist (NCEP), as well as a member of American Psychological Association, had successfully completed his PhD programme in Education Psychology at the University of Abuja.